cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SI

The paper discusses reasoning systems and their ability to consider potential negative side effects of their actions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of distributed semantic vector spaces learned from large text corpora is also discussed, which relates to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the limitations and biases of these approaches, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
